## Tailwind & DaisyUI

- Only use classes that are included by Tailwind's `content` globs configured in [tailwind.config.cjs](mdc:tailwind.config.cjs).
- Prefer semantic DaisyUI components (e.g., `btn`, `card`, `badge`) with Tailwind utilities for layout.
- Keep component class lists readable; split long class strings across multiple lines only in code, not in MD.
- Dark mode uses the `dark` theme defined in DaisyUI; avoid custom dark mode toggles unless needed.
